


Include comments in javadoc at class level and at method that identify the following:
-Thread safety or lack thereof
-Requirements / constraints that exist if/when subclasses of that class are created 
-heterogeneity vs. homogeneity in collections
-Lazy / on-demand creation of structures vs. implicit creation vs. explicit creation
-References using @see annotation

Can browse examples of excellant javadoc from the following:
-java.security.PermissionCollection





